George tries to hide that despite seeing every episode he has no idea what's happening on Game of Thrones. Elaine buys defective yoga pants.

Jerry swears off texting women. "I'm back to the phone! With the phone, you worry once a day and you're done. With texting, it never ends."
Kramer joins CrossFit and becomes insufferable. Elaine agrees to write George's OkCupid profile for him, but is way too honest in it.
A Game of Thrones quiz tells Jerry he'd be a Lannister no matter how many times he takes it. George sees his dad in an episode of Cathouse.
George doesn't believe Jason Collins is gay. G:"Wake up, Jerry! It's a scam. A lie for publicity so he can keep his job." J:"He's not you."
Elaine's bf is a "downgrader." "I call, he texts me back. I text, he emails. I'm scared if I email, I'll have to look for smoke signals."
George goes to the NFL Draft hoping to prove Mel Kiper's hair is fake. "I'm going to de-wig him, Jerry! That hair is an insult to the bald!"
Kramer and Newman search Brooklyn for a McDonald's rumored to carry the McRib year-round. A Twitter troll slowly drives Jerry crazy.
George changes his Bday on Facebook to see if people actually know it. No one does. "They're fakes,Jerry! I want the real deal or nothing!"
Elaine hates Arrested Development. Everyone judges her like she killed someone. J:"There are some things you're just not allowed to say."
Kramer becomes an obsessive, but almost always wrong wikipedia editor. George can't keep himself from texting women back right away.
Jerry's gf cries every time she listens to Adele. She constantly listens to Adele. Kramer dates a furry.
George tries to pick up a woman by claiming to be a cop that arrested a suspect in Boston case. CNN producer overhears it, runs it as fact.
Kramer discovers people in Brooklyn are dressing like him. George learns when you search his name, Google suggests "George Costanza Gay."
Elaine tries to build an Ikea dresser alone. E:"How hard can it be? It's just furniture." J:"With that attitude? I don't like your chances."
George goes crazy when his gf's chat window says she's "typing" for hours. He confronts her. Turns out she just bumped a key. She dumps him.
Kramer records bootleg DVD commentary for his favorite movies. Elaine's boyfriend is threatened when he sees her reading "Lean In."
Jerry's gf dumps him for not liking Beyonc?. J: "I mean sure she's pretty, but?" K:"You shut your mouth! She's an angel! An angel, Jerry!"
Kramer tries to help a bodega cat escape. Jerry notices that his gf isn't following him on Twitter, becomes obsessed with figuring out why.
Jerry dumps his gf for leaning on the pole on the subway. "What are you doing?! The pole is supposed to be shared. You're spooning with it!"
George discovers WebMD, is convinced he's dying. "Could I have cancer, malaria, AND smallpox? Because THAT'S WHAT THIS IS TELLING ME JERRY!"
Kramer starts an ebay store, becomes obsessed, and starts selling Jerry's things. J:"Where's my toaster?" K:"You still wanted that?"
Jerry tries to figure out whether a text from an ex at 11:55 was definitely about sex. "Ten minutes later, and I'd know for sure!"
Jerry discovers Newman squats on many famous names on Twitter. J:"Newman." N:"Oh not just Newman. I'm Clooney! I'm LeBron! I'm Tina Fey!"
George doubts the validity of a grocer's organic claims."He just puts a sticker on the regular fruit and BOOM! More expensive! It's a scam!"
Elaine dumps a guy who won't stop talking about how much better In-N-Out is than anything in New York. "We get it. You like their burgers!"

Jerry goes to Easter mass and dinner with his girlfriend. Her whole family looks at him whenever the Jews are mentioned.
Elaine dumps her bf when she catches him singing "We Are Young" in the shower. George becomes a "defender of gluten."
Newman repeatedly updates Jerry's Wikipedia page to say that he's gay. "No one's in charge of it! It's not an encyclopedia. It's chaos!"
Kramer creates an iPhone case that is itself a phone. "This way you can have an iPhone and a phone to actually make calls!"
George gets caught using his ex-girlfriend's roommate's father's HBOGo account. G:"Like you use your own." J:"I do, but then I'm an adult."

Elaine refuses to change her profile photo to support gay rights, because she finally likes her pic. Her bf dumps her for being a "bigot."
George dumps his gf because her coffee order is too long. "She wrote it for me once. It was a paragraph! You get one sentence, that's it!"
Elaine gets addicted to Pinterest DIY crafts. J "You're buying mason jars to make a lamp? Call me crazy, but you could just buy a lamp."
George gets a Kindle so women on the train will think he's smart. G:"I read sports articles! They think I'm reading? like?" J: "A book?"
Bania wants Jerry to co-star in a webseries with him on Funny or Die. BANIA:"How bout it, Jerry?" J:"Given those options... I'd pick die."
Jerry's girlfriend is way too entertained by the TV in the back of the Taxi. "Stop it! It's not entertainment. It's an annoyance!"
The only game Kramer correctly predicts is Florida Gulf Coast's win over Georgetown.  K:"The Eagles? I love the Eagles, Jerry!" J:"I quit."
Elaine lies on her online dating profile to sound classier. Jerry's new gf is obsessed with Pretty Little Liars, gets Jerry hooked.
Kramer gets stuck between subway cars for hours. George refuses to drink microbrews. "If they're so good, they'd brew more of them."
Jerry swears this is the year he'll win his March Madness bracket. Newman doesn't watch college basketball at all, wins the whole thing.
George dates the model who is the "face of Duane Reade." Kramer is furious to learn that she's not actually a pharmacist.

The voice of Kramer's car navigation system is so soothing it puts him to sleep.
Jerry keeps meeting women named Madison.
Elaine's bf keeps his phone out on the table during dinner. George keeps a list of restaurants that automatically add gratuity to the check.
George is offended that the woman next to him on a plane is wearing a surgical mask to avoid illness. "What, you're too good for my germs?!"
Jerry makes a joke about Taylor Swift on the tonight show. Swift writes a song about him. Elaine becomes overly invested in The Bachelor.
TMZ mistakenly reports that Jerry is near death. Newman is their anonymous source. "This says I'm dead, but I'm relatively sure I'm alive."
Kramer teaches pilates. Jerry receives a juicer from his gf but refuses to use it. "The smoothie is the boring cousin of the milkshake!"
Jerry's gf claims to be the model for the Starbucks logo. Elaine purposefully leaves her phone in a cab so she can see the hot cabbie again.
Kramer finds Iron Chef's discarded set & brings it back to his place. "I was going to put it in Jerry's but what would we judge? Cereal?!"
Jerry's parents video chat him but always call it "THE Skype," which slowly drives Jerry crazy. JERRY:"There's no 'the.' Stop adding 'the'!"
Kramer visits Rome, accidentally ends up sending up the wrong color smoke. Jerry tries to buy the Maestro's house in Tuscany.
George uses Craigslist to apartment hunt, ends up on a date w/ a man. J:"Did it say man for man?" G:"I thought he wanted a roommate, Jerry!"
Kramer starts delivering personal news to Jerry using black or white smoke. Elaine always gets stuck in the yoga class w/ the creep teacher.

Kramer and Jackie Chiles' case against the NYC soda ban gets the law overturned. Kramer thinks Bloomberg is having him followed.
Jerry and Elaine discover George is an "abbreviation texter" with women. Kramer becomes obsessed with who the next Pope will be.

Elaine's Republican boyfriend says "Thanks a lot, Obama," whenever something bad happens. Kramer claims to have created ChristianMingle.
